37:30.848 --> 37:36.375
And this church, these series of churches were Greek churches, primarily Gentile.

37:36.896 --> 37:38.738
That is non-Jewish churches.

37:38.978 --> 37:45.828
And the Scripture, particularly in the first five verses that I read, we learned some things about these Macedonian Christians.

37:45.908 --> 37:53.900
And my question is, could they be said of Salem Fields Community Church in the same way that they were said of the Macedonian churches?

37:54.942 --> 38:02.132
As I read this passage of Scripture, they were developing into a they gave church.

38:02.853 --> 38:06.098
That's how they were described, they gave.

38:06.498 --> 38:24.199
And I wonder if it would be appropriate for us to think for a moment about what it might be like for this church to continue that process of giving so that when somebody says, tell me about Salem Community, Salem Fields Community Church, people would say they gave.

38:24.980 --> 38:30.947
When you look at this passage of Scripture in verses one and two, we realize that they gave generously.

38:32.229 --> 38:33.490
They gave generously.

38:33.570 --> 38:41.478
And now brothers and sisters, we want you to know about the grace that God has given the Macedonian church in the midst of a very severe trial.

38:42.259 --> 38:49.947
Their overflowing joy and their extreme poverty weld up in rich generosity.

38:51.368 --> 38:58.075
The Macedonian churches were poor by the standards of the world, but they were extremely generous.

38:58.115 --> 39:01.138
They were open-handed with their wealth.

39:01.570 --> 39:03.632
with other Christians that were in need.

39:04.173 --> 39:05.755
You say, well, what was the great need?

39:05.815 --> 39:14.085
Well, there was an incredible famine that had hit Jerusalem and it had impacted the church there, and the Macedonian church responded.

39:14.205 --> 39:24.818
And even though we read about the Macedonian church that we're experiencing tough circumstances and extreme financial need, they were willing to give to others.

39:25.378 --> 39:29.463
They were encouraged to be faithful in their giving.

39:29.763 --> 39:34.129
And the Macedonian Christians helped despite the fact that they had problems of their own.

39:34.189 --> 39:39.916
And even though they had difficulty in their own financial condition, they gave to others.

39:41.538 --> 39:45.743
The Macedonian Christians helped despite the fact that they had problems of their own.

39:46.443 --> 39:48.085
They themselves were extremely poor.

39:48.566 --> 39:51.229
They had endured a great deal of persecution.

39:51.790 --> 39:55.154
In many ways, they should have been the one receiving the help.

39:56.290 --> 39:57.972
but instead they were the ones giving it.

39:58.792 --> 40:06.280
Don't show your hands, but have you ever thought to yourself and our pastor is always talking to us about giving and offering so that others will have a need met?

40:06.961 --> 40:16.790
Don't raise your hand, but have you ever thought to yourself, man, I wish there was a church somewhere that on some Sunday they would take an offering and send it to our church because we need help.

40:17.931 --> 40:24.498
Macedonian people gave generously and willingly to help the Christians in Jerusalem.

40:25.666 --> 40:30.893
The Scripture text doesn't suggest it, but they never ask, well, do you think they really deserve it?

40:32.055 --> 40:38.243
Is this a situation that they've gotten themselves into and that if they've gotten themselves into it, they should get themselves out of it?

40:38.423 --> 40:39.304
No, they gave.

40:39.364 --> 40:42.849
They gave very faithfully.

40:43.230 --> 40:47.155
But if you go on and look in verse 3, they gave sacrificially.

40:48.477 --> 40:55.346
That is to say, they gave even though they were experiencing extreme poverty.

40:56.386 --> 40:59.830
The language in this passage of Scripture is very interesting.

41:00.331 --> 41:03.735
That word means rock, bottom, destitution.

41:04.616 --> 41:06.037
He said, I'm not sure if I understand that.

41:06.077 --> 41:07.359
Let me see if I explained it this way.

41:07.859 --> 41:13.426
Payday is Friday and the resources are already limited by Tuesday.

41:13.486 --> 41:20.594
That's, that's where they found themselves.

41:21.698 --> 41:32.193
The word that's used here is the word that's used to describe a beggar who has absolutely nothing and no hope of getting anything, yet despite their situation they were willing to give.

41:32.253 --> 41:38.442
So sacrificial giving has nothing to do with your income or your bank account.

41:39.704 --> 41:46.674
It has everything to do with your commitment to being obedient to what God says for you to do.

41:47.138 --> 41:53.047
If you go on and look in verses three and four, they gave voluntarily.

41:56.272 --> 42:01.180
They gave as they were able and even beyond their ability, entirely on their own.

42:01.760 --> 42:09.272
I was reading a story this week about Leighton Farrell, who was the minister of Highland Park Church in Dallas for many years.

42:09.312 --> 42:12.417
You may not recognize that name, but a very substantial church.

42:12.938 --> 42:15.762
Early in his ministry, he tells of a man

42:16.002 --> 42:19.026
who came to him when they were both very, very young.

42:20.228 --> 42:27.598
And when they met together, this man and this pastor made a covenant that they would tithe on their income.

42:28.619 --> 42:30.061
They would tithe 10%.

42:30.622 --> 42:45.202
They were both young and neither of them had much money, but things changed very dramatically for the man, not so much for the pastor, and the man that talked to the pastor who established the covenant with the pastor that they would both tithe

42:45.282 --> 42:51.914
on their income, found it very easily to tithe $1,000 when he earned $10,000.

42:53.397 --> 43:09.106
Matter of fact, $10,000 was fairly easy the year that he earned $100,000, and $100,000 was a little more difficult when he earned a million dollars.

43:10.114 --> 43:19.524
But the year that he earned $6 million, he found it very, very difficult to write that check for $600,000 to the church.

43:21.246 --> 43:23.308
So he called his longtime minister friend.

43:23.328 --> 43:28.073
They had not seen each other in about 20 years and the minister had moved on to another church.

43:28.494 --> 43:36.963
But the man asked to see the minister with whom he had established this covenant that he would continue to faithfully give in tithes to the church.

43:38.365 --> 43:39.666
And they met at a restaurant

43:40.418 --> 43:48.007
The pastor had no idea what was up and the man sat down at the booth and he said, I need to be let out of the covenant.

43:48.388 --> 43:50.430
This tithing business has got to stop.

43:50.530 --> 43:57.439
It was fine when my tithe was $1,000, but now it is $600,000.

43:59.501 --> 44:01.664
Pastor, you've got to do something.

44:03.346 --> 44:09.874
The pastor stepped out of the booth and knelt down right in the restaurant and bowed his head and began to pray.

44:10.530 --> 44:16.317
The man was embarrassed because he couldn't imagine what the pastor was praying silently about for so long.

44:16.838 --> 44:21.063
And eventually he tapped him on the shoulder and he said to the pastor, what are you doing?

44:21.644 --> 44:24.447
He said, I hope you're praying that God would let me out of this covenant.

44:25.449 --> 44:35.281
The pastor said, no, he said, I'm praying that God will reduce your income back to the point where you felt comfortable to pay your tithe.

44:36.642 --> 44:39.506
You say, that's a crazy story, but I want to tell you

44:41.122 --> 44:46.027
When we learn to give voluntarily, God opens up the windows for us.

44:46.708 --> 44:50.072
The Macedonians gave freely and willingly.

44:50.172 --> 44:59.121
Matter of fact, in verse 4, it says, they urgently pleaded with us for the privilege of sharing in this service to the Lord's people.

44:59.161 --> 45:10.994
Now, I don't know about your church, but all the churches I've ever pastored, I've never had somebody come to me and say, pastor, oh please, oh please, can we participate and give more money?

45:12.034 --> 45:13.416
We just want to give more money.

45:14.357 --> 45:15.538
We just want to give more money.

45:16.660 --> 45:21.425
Matter of fact, usually what happens is when it's time to take an offering, people kind of step back.

45:23.928 --> 45:31.938
These Macedonias did not have much money, yet they pleaded with the apostle to take what they had and use it.

45:32.719 --> 45:41.970
Recently I was in a church board meeting and it was a church that had been fairly contentious and I wasn't sure what was going on and finally at the meeting I said,

45:42.306 --> 45:45.830
Can you talk to me about ways that God is moving in your church?

45:45.850 --> 45:54.939
And I was hoping just for one activity of the Spirit of God in the life of their church and finally a man kind of leaned back in his chair and he crossed his arms.

45:55.279 --> 45:56.381
That's never a good sign.

45:57.302 --> 45:58.423
And he said this to me.

45:58.443 --> 46:04.529
He said, well, Dr. Bowser, I just want to tell you, we've stopped taking and offering on Sundays in our church.

46:06.311 --> 46:07.192
I was shocked.

46:08.173 --> 46:09.394
I thought, how do you pay?

46:09.666 --> 46:12.651
your pastor and pay your mortgage and pay your utilities.

46:13.312 --> 46:18.561
Then he went on to tell me they felt like the offering was an interruption in their worship, the worship flow.

46:20.725 --> 46:24.371
And then he kind of smiled and relaxed his arms and he said, I'll tell you what we've done.

46:24.391 --> 46:27.416
We've put a box in the back on the wall.

46:28.137 --> 46:35.730
And as people go out and exit the worship space, we encourage them to give as their last act of worship before they leave the service.

46:37.314 --> 46:39.497
And I thought to myself, that's genius.

46:40.739 --> 46:46.949
Then he said this, he said, our giving is going up 30% this year.

46:47.009 --> 46:53.119
The district where I serve, we have a number of Latino churches and Haitian churches.

46:53.179 --> 46:55.082
I love how they take the offering.

46:55.963 --> 47:03.355
They put an offering plate right in front and they say, okay, it's time to give and everybody has to get up and move forward and give.

47:03.755 --> 47:05.458
And I'm talking about peer pressure.

47:08.578 --> 47:10.841
But here's the, here's the most incredible thing.

47:10.861 --> 47:24.822
They have little children and the parents give them an offering and they walk to the front and they drop the offering in the plate and they're being trained early to be generous people.

47:26.404 --> 47:30.610
Verse five says this, they gave wholeheartedly.

47:34.210 --> 47:36.632
They exceeded our expectations, the Scripture says.

47:36.692 --> 47:40.896
They gave themselves first of all to the Lord and then by the will of God to us also.

47:42.137 --> 47:47.903
You see, their heart went first and their generosity followed.

47:48.864 --> 47:57.732
If our hearts are truly devoted to the Master, if our hearts are truly committed to God, then the act of worship and giving will follow.

47:59.594 --> 48:04.178
And so I've been wrestling with this passage of Scripture, knowing I would be here to share this with you today.

48:04.674 --> 48:15.145
And so I've been asking myself this key question, and it's a simple question, and that is, how does God accomplish His purposes today?

48:15.205 --> 48:19.029
How does God work today?

48:19.089 --> 48:25.835
And I believe that a missionary church is God's primary way of accomplishing His purposes on earth.

48:26.416 --> 48:27.337
Let me tell you a story.

48:27.377 --> 48:32.402
The year was 1653, and Oliver Cromwell had placed a

48:32.546 --> 48:37.773
his own stern version of Christianity upon upon his people and upon the pastors of England.

48:37.813 --> 48:42.860
Matter of fact, it was so difficult that many churches fell into disuse and disrepair.

48:43.160 --> 48:48.227
Many pastors were run out of town and flocks lost their shepherd.

48:48.267 --> 48:55.677
Many people removed, pastors were removed from their office as pastor and they were forbidden to practice their faith.

48:55.777 --> 48:59.042
And in that time in England, only three churches were built.

49:00.463 --> 49:02.386
One of them was paid for by

49:02.754 --> 49:08.345
Sir Robert Shirley, a man named Shirley, paid for one of those churches.

49:09.207 --> 49:13.214
And the church that he paid for was the Stanton Herald Church.

49:14.437 --> 49:25.458
And as the donor, he wanted to make sure that it served as a place, as a house for the Lord and a refuge for some of the earthly shepherds that had been displaced from their churches.

49:26.658 --> 49:29.261
And the construction of this church did not please Cromwell.

49:29.301 --> 49:33.325
Matter of fact, it made Cromwell so angry that he sent Shirley a message.

49:33.705 --> 49:35.046
And let me just paraphrase it.

49:35.607 --> 49:36.808
It simply went like this.

49:38.250 --> 49:41.893
If you have money to build a church, you have money to help in the war effort.

49:41.933 --> 49:46.798
Matter of fact, the money you used to build that church could be used to build a ship in the war.

49:48.920 --> 49:54.546
So Robert Shirley thought that paying for a church was more important.

49:54.690 --> 49:59.176
than underwriting a regiment for war, and he refused to allocate his resources.

49:59.958 --> 50:03.623
He just simply told Cromwell, I will not do it.

50:04.925 --> 50:14.418
And for his refusal, a man named Shirley was sent to the tower of London where his enemies poisoned him, and at age 23, he died.

50:14.438 --> 50:19.926
So that's a very bleak story for a man named Shirley.

50:20.887 --> 50:22.770
And in truth, he would be a forgotten

50:23.330 --> 50:32.041
point in the history of England, if it had not been for the people of his parish, that benefited from the church that he had built.

50:34.163 --> 50:41.993
This church, if you were to go there today, there is an inscription in the stone, and it says this, and you'd find this very interesting.

50:42.474 --> 50:52.626
In 1653, when all things sacred in the kingdom were either profaned or demolished, this church

50:52.834 --> 50:58.963
was built to do the best of things in the worst of times.

51:03.449 --> 51:12.682
I don't know about you, but I want to be a part of a church just like that that does the best of things in the worst of times.

51:13.843 --> 51:17.288
Don't look now, but we are in the worst of times.

51:18.870 --> 51:21.554
God has raised up this church, a missionary church,

51:22.242 --> 51:26.629
to do the best of things in the worst of times.

51:27.430 --> 51:45.057
In 1 Corinthians chapter 12, verse 12, Paul uses some language that I want you to hear as we set up and think about not just this man named Shirley, but a crazy church, but to set up and think about Bruce Springsteen.

51:46.038 --> 51:48.562
I know that sounds super spiritual on a Sunday morning.

51:50.114 --> 52:00.929
But this is the passage of Scripture that says this, just as a body, though one has many parts, all of its parts form one body, so it is with Christ.

52:02.431 --> 52:11.763
Missionary churches are generous churches, and it is the generosity of everyone that make a difference.

52:12.264 --> 52:16.850
Recently I was watching a Bruce Springsteen and E Street band concert.

52:17.602 --> 52:20.146
Don't look at me like you've never listened to Bruce Springsteen.

52:20.386 --> 52:25.354
Don't act like this is a shock because many of us here could name the songs.

52:25.975 --> 52:28.338
And I saw something that helped me think about generosity.

52:28.579 --> 52:31.203
Matter of fact, it kind of reminded me of your church.

52:32.364 --> 52:34.808
And it reminded me of the goal of $70,000.

52:36.611 --> 52:40.357
It also says something about how a missionary church might operate.

52:42.480 --> 52:43.922
Bruce Springsteen is

52:44.322 --> 52:47.825
with his band, and they're gonna play a song that they have not rehearsed before.

52:48.326 --> 52:50.588
It's a song they used to play years and years ago.

52:50.608 --> 53:03.480
I want you to watch his band, and I want you to watch Bruce Springsteen as he tries to get in the right key, set the right tone, and the sound of the song that they're gonna play.

53:03.740 --> 53:04.061
Watch.

53:06.643 --> 53:13.970
Every night we try to pull one out that we haven't played since we were, I don't know, 16.

53:15.810 --> 53:19.627
If maybe so, let's see how we do it.

53:21.254 --> 53:25.010
Let's get a good key.

54:06.050 --> 54:09.377
All right, let's see how we do.

54:09.437 --> 54:10.118
Give me some slack.

54:15.430 --> 54:16.432
Well, I did it.

54:16.452 --> 54:17.734
Maybe I'm a little over ambitious.

54:17.774 --> 54:19.538
Give me a cable.

55:08.226 --> 55:09.107
You see what's happening here?

55:09.647 --> 55:20.598
The leader is trying to convince the band of the song they're going to sing, the tempo of the song, the rhythm of the song, the key that the song is going to be in.

55:20.658 --> 55:35.092
It's interesting because the leader hears this $70,000 goal ringing through his head and the Philippines and Nigeria and India.

55:36.673 --> 55:37.714
And we're the band.

55:37.826 --> 55:40.373
We're the congregation.

55:41.255 --> 55:44.303
Bruce Springsteen is trying to convince his band that are all very capable.

55:44.604 --> 55:45.707
Understand music theory.

55:46.048 --> 55:49.056
He's trying to get them on the same page.

55:49.898 --> 55:54.290
Watch what happens.

56:39.554 --> 56:42.558
hasn't sung the song yet, but you can hear it, can't you?

56:43.760 --> 56:45.643
He hasn't sung a word of the song.

56:45.663 --> 56:46.765
He's just singing it.

56:47.105 --> 56:56.239
And did you notice how the people in the audience begin to smile and they begin to react and they begin to respond as they begin to get the picture of what's about to happen?

56:56.780 --> 57:02.328
And when I see this, I'm reminded of what Bruce Springsteen said to his band, try it, boys.

57:03.750 --> 57:04.411
Follow me.

57:05.252 --> 57:06.354
This is the vision.

57:07.938 --> 57:09.669
Then he says, here we go.

57:09.709 --> 57:13.874
Listen now.

58:11.138 --> 58:13.241
sudden you begin to be swept up in the music.

58:13.682 --> 58:36.498
You begin to realize this is going to happen and the song is playing and the vision is unfolding and you begin to get the idea that I'm a part of this and I have something to contribute and he then begins to invite each of the instruments to play and this is where it gets very interesting because without any music, without anything in front of them,

58:36.642 --> 58:44.148
Just listening to the vision of the leader and listening to the song, each of them begin to contribute.

58:44.249 --> 58:48.082
Watch.

01:01:17.570 --> 01:01:21.816
This is a picture of the church functioning as a missionary church.

01:01:22.717 --> 01:01:30.288
Every person playing the instrument that God has given them and being generous with that resource.

01:01:31.370 --> 01:01:36.677
You say to yourself, I can't play the saxophone, I can't sing, I can't play.

01:01:38.620 --> 01:01:43.227
Let me show you one more clip and you're going to have to catch it very, very quick.

01:01:43.247 --> 01:01:45.650
It involves a cowbell.

01:01:47.874 --> 01:01:52.018
you

01:02:27.298 --> 01:02:30.562
How many of you thought you'd see Bruce Springsteen in church this morning?

01:02:31.804 --> 01:02:40.696
In between the first service and the second service, we got a message somebody was watching online and wanted to know if Bruce Springsteen was here this morning.

01:02:41.918 --> 01:02:42.819
The answer is no.

01:02:44.822 --> 01:02:49.908
Could I just say to you, every person in this church is needed.

01:02:51.671 --> 01:02:57.138
Every person in the church can be generous.

01:02:57.410 --> 01:03:00.495
with the resources that God has given you.

01:03:01.096 --> 01:03:04.521
Salem Fields Community Church.

01:03:06.664 --> 01:03:11.551
And Stanton Herald Church are the same church.

01:03:12.493 --> 01:03:26.514
You do not have an inscription outside as Stanton Herald Church does, but if it was there, could it be said just like this, instead of the year 1653,

01:03:27.266 --> 01:03:37.138
What would it be like in the year of 2021 when all things sacred in the kingdom were either profaned or demolished?

01:03:38.540 --> 01:03:46.049
Salem Fields Community Church was built to do the best of things in the worst of times.

01:03:47.411 --> 01:03:48.132
Think about that.

01:03:49.354 --> 01:03:56.082
That takes a missionary church that is generous, not just to the elementary school,

01:03:56.610 --> 01:04:07.103
not just to the Commonwealth of Virginia, but to the outer reaches of India and the Philippines and Nigeria.

01:04:08.404 --> 01:04:14.912
And can you believe God has invited us to partner with him in that task?

01:04:15.373 --> 01:04:16.274
May God bless you.

01:04:19.277 --> 01:04:19.858
Thank you, David.

01:04:27.202 --> 01:04:30.868
I love that Bruce Springsteen illustration.

01:04:30.948 --> 01:04:36.898
When he first played it and Bruce was trying to find his key, I was like, where is this going?

01:04:38.660 --> 01:04:39.642
But you see what happens?

01:04:40.423 --> 01:04:54.706
When everybody joins in, when everybody's using their gifts, when everybody's participating, something that sounds really terrible in the beginning begins to be something that is just amazing.

01:04:55.266 --> 01:05:04.557
And so what we're doing these days at Salem Fields is we're trying to move forward this vision of people belonging, believing, and becoming.

01:05:05.479 --> 01:05:08.502
And not just here in Spotsylvania County, but around the globe.

01:05:09.424 --> 01:05:12.607
The Thanksgiving offering is not something that's for here.

01:05:12.647 --> 01:05:15.731
We're doing for Spotsie here in different things like that here.

01:05:16.152 --> 01:05:24.402
But we're talking about taking the message of hope to 156 world areas, including Nigeria.

01:05:24.802 --> 01:05:27.006
in India, in the Philippines.

01:05:27.487 --> 01:05:33.638
You see some of the things that are happening in these places because of you, because of your generosity.

01:05:34.480 --> 01:05:39.168
Manu Kubati, who is leading our work in India, and he's watching today.

01:05:39.208 --> 01:05:39.910
How you doing, Manu?

01:05:40.270 --> 01:05:41.252
He's watching today.

01:05:41.272 --> 01:05:44.498
He constantly is in communication with me.

01:05:45.378 --> 01:05:55.351
And it's been amazing to see how pastors that couldn't eat and their families couldn't eat because of the pandemic and because people are day laborers and they work during the day.

01:05:55.471 --> 01:06:00.137
And because everything was closed down, they couldn't get work, which meant they couldn't eat.

01:06:00.217 --> 01:06:08.527
And because you gave last year in the Thanksgiving offering, he could take food and he could bring food to those pastoral families.

01:06:08.587 --> 01:06:10.770
He could bring food to children.

01:06:11.106 --> 01:06:20.650
because you gave and Nigeria, the ministry that we've been involved in with James and Charity for the longest and the soccer camps that they're doing there.

01:06:20.850 --> 01:06:23.858
Things are really, really tough in Nigeria.

01:06:23.970 --> 01:06:25.372
things are really toughened.

01:06:25.552 --> 01:06:26.834
There's political unrest there.

01:06:26.854 --> 01:06:28.295
There's religious unrest there.

01:06:28.576 --> 01:06:31.259
They also have COVID-19 happening there.

01:06:31.299 --> 01:06:41.392
But because you continue to give, because you gave last year, they are able to educate and give kids a place to kind of experience being a kid.

01:06:41.472 --> 01:06:45.517
And they've been able to feed kids there because you gave.

01:06:45.577 --> 01:06:52.626
And then our newest, our newest partnership for Pastor Kelly, our global, our global,

01:06:52.802 --> 01:06:54.705
campus pastor in the Philippines.

01:06:55.486 --> 01:07:00.714
I don't know if you've been keeping up with them, but they got their first safe house and they're renovating it.

01:07:00.754 --> 01:07:19.762
And their young kids who need shelter, who need safety from human trafficking will be able to come out of that lifestyle and come to that safe house and get a good job and be free because you give.

01:07:20.226 --> 01:07:36.324
And not just those three places, but we partner with a number of churches and 156 world areas so that people all around the world may belong, believe, and become.

01:07:38.046 --> 01:07:39.707
And so you know how this works.

01:07:40.248 --> 01:07:45.594
There's a card there on the seat in front of you, near you somewhere in that card.

01:07:45.654 --> 01:07:49.458
We're just asking you to make a pledge, a pledge between you and God,

01:07:49.698 --> 01:07:50.199
Here's the deal.

01:07:50.499 --> 01:07:53.343
You don't have to sign it, because I don't want to know who did it.

01:07:53.363 --> 01:07:55.726
I just want to know where we are in the pledge giving.

01:07:56.446 --> 01:07:57.328
If you want to, you can.

01:07:57.388 --> 01:07:58.589
If you don't want to, you don't have to.

01:07:58.870 --> 01:07:59.951
You can do it online.

01:08:00.171 --> 01:08:05.137
There are a number of ways you can get the information to us, but we want you to get it to us so we know how we're doing.

01:08:06.699 --> 01:08:14.109
Here's one of the creative ways that I've decided to do it, because the meta, the new Facebook, anybody know that Facebook changed this name, the meta?

01:08:14.529 --> 01:08:15.551
Well, here's the deal.

01:08:15.831 --> 01:08:18.354
They're going to match up to $8 million.

01:08:18.658 --> 01:08:22.442
given to non-profits up until giving Tuesday.

01:08:23.764 --> 01:08:24.805
Now this is interesting.

01:08:25.265 --> 01:08:30.811
What are the chances that you could give something and have your money doubled by Facebook?

01:08:31.552 --> 01:08:32.353
So here's what I did.

01:08:32.393 --> 01:08:33.634
I have a site.

01:08:33.975 --> 01:08:40.502
If you go to my Facebook account, I have a site there called Salem Fields Global Connection.

01:08:40.923 --> 01:08:43.385
And I would go $5,000.

01:08:43.525 --> 01:08:47.730
I already have like a thousand in the two days.

01:08:48.514 --> 01:08:49.656
And so here's the deal.

01:08:49.676 --> 01:08:53.922
I just, I'm just trying to get my friends, the people who know me.

01:08:54.483 --> 01:08:55.945
I mean, who wouldn't want to give to kids?

01:08:56.686 --> 01:09:03.917
Who wouldn't want to give so the kids can eat, so the kids can be safe, so the kids can live somewhere in a positive environment.

01:09:03.937 --> 01:09:04.838
Who wouldn't want to do that?

01:09:05.379 --> 01:09:06.581
People are giving all the time.

01:09:07.082 --> 01:09:07.662
Why not?

01:09:08.323 --> 01:09:10.166
To seven fields, global, connect.

01:09:11.388 --> 01:09:15.875
And so even if I raise 2,500, it becomes 5,000, because it gets doubled.

01:09:16.395 --> 01:09:18.098
Maybe you have some friends on,

01:09:18.274 --> 01:09:21.457
Maybe this is a creative way to God will use you.

01:09:21.657 --> 01:09:22.038
Here's the deal.

01:09:22.058 --> 01:09:23.039
I don't know what God wants to do.

01:09:23.239 --> 01:09:25.882
Maybe God will have you do something else creative.

01:09:26.662 --> 01:09:27.343
But here's the deal.

01:09:28.204 --> 01:09:41.917
I believe that the $70,000 that we will raise this year between now and March 31st will connect, will allow us to connect with some people so they belong, believe, and become.

01:09:42.678 --> 01:09:46.482
And I believe with all my heart,

01:09:47.074 --> 01:09:51.479
that what we do here impacts spots and beyond.

01:09:51.499 --> 01:09:57.387
I believe they're people who will eat because you give.

01:09:58.388 --> 01:10:00.090
I mean, I got pictures I can show you.

01:10:01.251 --> 01:10:03.814
They're people who will be in safety because you give.

01:10:05.156 --> 01:10:05.877
These are our folks.

01:10:05.917 --> 01:10:07.899
These are folks that we support.

01:10:08.280 --> 01:10:13.486
James and Charity, Manu Kubati, you know, Pastor Kelly, these are people you support.

01:10:13.526 --> 01:10:16.690
These people you help do the mission.

01:10:17.346 --> 01:10:20.050
I'm so glad that this is a generous church.

01:10:20.110 --> 01:10:21.953
It was a generous church way before I got here.

01:10:22.874 --> 01:10:27.140
I'm just kind of stepping in the steps, footsteps of folks who preceded me.

01:10:28.042 --> 01:10:34.952
So sometime this week, feel that cut out, drop it in the offering box if you want to.

01:10:35.592 --> 01:10:39.138
Anyway, however you do it, get it to us so we know where we are.

01:10:39.178 --> 01:10:41.361
Thank you for being generous.

01:10:42.242 --> 01:10:44.946
Thank you for all that you do for Spotsie and Beyond.

01:10:45.538 --> 01:10:54.667
You have a pastor much like Bruce Springsteen that sometimes just sits back and watches a generous church in action.

01:10:56.589 --> 01:10:57.690
And thanks God for you.

01:10:58.671 --> 01:11:01.113
So there are a lot of things that I'm thankful for this Thanksgiving.

01:11:01.914 --> 01:11:07.599
I'm thankful to be a pastor of a church that's just generous.

01:11:07.739 --> 01:11:08.740
I thank God for you.

01:11:09.441 --> 01:11:11.323
I thank God for what he's doing in your life.

01:11:13.024 --> 01:11:14.866
And I thank God that

01:11:15.266 --> 01:11:17.368
that he's gonna do even more.

01:11:17.408 --> 01:11:23.715
As we say, Lord, be exalted in our lives.

01:11:24.376 --> 01:11:25.457
Let me pray for you and let you go.

01:11:25.497 --> 01:11:27.039
Father, thank you so much for this day.

01:11:27.059 --> 01:11:29.101
Thank you so much for this word.

01:11:29.121 --> 01:11:31.384
This is a good word.

01:11:31.904 --> 01:11:36.429
Father, have you longed to be exalted in our lives?

01:11:37.270 --> 01:11:39.793
You longed to be magnified in our lives.

01:11:40.754 --> 01:11:44.498
And Father, part of that is just us saying, God, here I am.

01:11:46.914 --> 01:11:48.055
be magnified in me.

01:11:50.478 --> 01:12:04.733
And Father, I realize that when I surrender my life to you, you get my wallet and my investments, you get my checkbook, you get my cash app, you get everything else that belongs to me.

01:12:05.514 --> 01:12:16.626
And so Father, would you help us to be the kind of people that you can trust with folks all over the globe who have no place to belong?

01:12:17.954 --> 01:12:22.561
You've created them to belong with you and the body, but they have no place to belong.

01:12:23.342 --> 01:12:26.967
Thank you for entrusting us to make that possible in their lives.

01:12:27.788 --> 01:12:40.126
We thank you for all that you have done, all that you are doing this very day and what you are going to do through the resources of your people in the days that come.

01:12:40.747 --> 01:12:43.651
We love you and we give you praise, amen, and amen.

01:12:44.012 --> 01:12:45.153
Happy Thanksgiving to you guys.

01:12:45.193 --> 01:12:45.734
Thanks for coming.

01:12:45.754 --> 01:12:46.155
Love you guys.

01:12:46.575 --> 01:12:47.136
Have a great one.

